flowRoot.flowPara: 5 Reduce nodes receive key-value pairs from (multiple) mappers, which are grouped by key, before applying the reduce function to each group. All key-value pairs sharing a key are sent to the same reducer, so all error messages designated with the 'err' key, propagate to the same reducer. In this figure the reduce stage represents the reduce nodes operation on a single key and corresponding list of values; in general a reduce node may perform several of these operations, one for every unique key it receives.
8Errors here can take one of two forms:
a) Individual errors occuring from an error thrown in the reducer, or from a reducer timeout. e.g. ('err',(R2,TimeoutError))
b) Errors from the sense and map stage which were aggregated and passed on by a reducer, e.g. as shown in note 3.

A final two-step merging of errors and successes is performed here. First, one-off errors arising at the reduce stage are merged with the prior error key - error message list. Then, all pairs of keys and reduced values are merged to one data structure and returned.

4 Each mapper emits key-value pairs which are aech sent to one reduce node based on the hash function of the key. Here we symbolically show the map function sending both to the a shown reducer, as well as potentially to other reducers in the DAG.
